---
// The Total Experience Design™ framework diagram + intro text. Used on the home page.
---

<section class="container" id="framework">
  <div class="section-title reveal">
    <div class="section-title__label">IV002 — The Framework</div>
    <h2 class="section-title__title">
      Total Experience Design™ holds the <em>whole picture</em> together.
    </h2>
  </div>

  <div class="diagram-wrap reveal">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 700 640" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Total Experience Design framework: Human Foundation, Vision, Master Planning, Realisation surrounding Spatial, Technology, Brand & Digital, Content with Time at the centre.">
      <circle cx="350" cy="320" r="240" fill="none" stroke="#000" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4 6" opacity="0.35"/>
      <path d="M 350 100 A 220 220 0 0 1 570 320" fill="none" stroke="#000" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.55" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
      <path d="M 570 320 A 220 220 0 0 1 350 540" fill="none" stroke="#000" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.55" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
      <path d="M 350 540 A 220 220 0 0 1 130 320" fill="none" stroke="#000" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.55" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
      <path d="M 130 320 A 220 220 0 0 1 350 100" fill="none" stroke="#3D2EB8" stroke-width="2.5" opacity="0.95" marker-end="url(#arrowBlue)"/>
      <defs>
        <marker id="arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="6" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto-start-reverse">
          <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="#000" opacity="0.55"/>
        </marker>
        <marker id="arrowBlue" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="6" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse">
          <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="#3D2EB8"/>
        </marker>
      </defs>
      <g>
        <rect x="270" y="40" width="160" height="40" fill="#82FFC0" rx="2"/>
        <text x="350" y="66" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-weight="600" font-size="15">Human Foundation</text>
        <text x="600" y="325" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-weight="600" font-size="16" text-anchor="start">Vision</text>
        <rect x="270" y="560" width="160" height="40" fill="#C8B4DC" rx="2"/>
        <text x="350" y="586" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-weight="600" font-size="15">Master Planning</text>
        <text x="100" y="325" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-weight="600" font-size="16" text-anchor="end">Realisation</text>
      </g>
      <g>
        <circle cx="270" cy="240" r="78" fill="#F2EDD8" stroke="#000" stroke-width="1"/>
        <text x="270" y="246" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-weight="600" font-size="16">Spatial</text>
        <circle cx="430" cy="240" r="78" fill="#F2EDD8" stroke="#000" stroke-width="1"/>
        <text x="430" y="246" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-weight="600" font-size="16">Technology</text>
        <circle cx="270" cy="400" r="78" fill="#F2EDD8" stroke="#000" stroke-width="1"/>
        <text x="270" y="398" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-weight="600" font-size="15">Brand</text>
        <text x="270" y="418" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-weight="600" font-size="15">&amp; Digital</text>
        <circle cx="430" cy="400" r="78" fill="#F2EDD8" stroke="#000" stroke-width="1"/>
        <text x="430" y="408" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-weight="600" font-size="16">Content</text>
      </g>
      <g>
        <rect x="332" y="302" width="36" height="36" fill="#3D2EB8" rx="2"/>
        <text x="350" y="325" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="#82FFC0" font-weight="600" letter-spacing="0.5">TIME</text>
      </g>
    </svg>

    <div class="diagram-text">
      <h3>Five pillars. Four phases. <em>One continuous process.</em></h3>
      <p>
        Total Experience Design™ is a complete operating system for places. It binds the
        five disciplines that shape how a space feels — Spatial, Technology, Brand &amp;
        Digital, Content, and Time — to the four phases that govern how it gets made:
        Vision, Master Planning, Realisation, and the Human Foundation it all returns to.
      </p>
      <p>
        Time sits at the centre because experiences unfold. A place is not a product
        shipped on a date; it is a system that must perform from opening day through
        every season that follows.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
